uired since the focus is on class and method names, and `setLanguage` similarly falls outside the scope. The knowledge file appears clean overall; while the 要求 section is omitted, its content is fully captured in the 特徴 section and implementation details, so this is an acceptable omission. Let me finalize my assessment that there are no critical findings to report. Looking at the source code example more carefully, I can see it demonstrates how `formatMessage()` behaves differently depending on whether the thread context language is set or a specific locale is passed as an argument. The knowledge file appears to have truncated this example, cutting off mid-way through the message creation and missing the full demonstration of the three different invocation patterns that show the language resolution hierarchy.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20468,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20468,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6f84b7ee-2f16-46b3-bc7b-6ad9b064be9b","uuid":"d9c36597-4cd0-4f93-9d69-84b1719eed6f"}
